<p>My team, 1305, has recently gotten a swerve drive train that we have been working on. We are using the Max Swerve modules from Rev. One thing I have noticed is that the wheels reset after joystick inputs, and I have trying a couple of ways to stop that, but none have worked so far, any ideas?</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":24,"updated_at":"2023-12-19T04:18:59.098Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":149,"reads":314,"readers_count":313,"score":837.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":446559,"topic_slug":"stopping-swerve-wheels-from-resetting-their-position-after-every-joystick-input","display_username":"Inuka Silva","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":61666,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"1305 Alumn"},"post_url":"/t/stopping-swerve-wheels-from-resetting-their-position-after-every-joystick-input/446559/1","custom_user_title":"1305 Alumn","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3266870,"name":"Fletch","username":"Fletch1373","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/fletch1373/{size}/220073_2.png","created_at":"2023-12-19T05:17:18.425Z","cooked":"<p>Thats almost certainly a code problem.  Can you share a link to your code (preferably the whole project on github or similar)?</p>
<p>Also, did you use the REV starter template, or something else (e.g. YAGSL)?</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":24,"updated_at":"2023-12-19T05:18:09.426Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":301,"readers_count":300,"score":90.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":446559,"topic_slug":"stopping-swerve-wheels-from-resetting-their-position-after-every-joystick-input","display_username":"Fletch","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":9105,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"3181/3015 Mentor | 213/1373 Alum | CSA/FTAA/Jack-of-all-Trades"},"post_url":"/t/stopping-swerve-wheels-from-resetting-their-position-after-every-joystick-input/446559/2","custom_user_title":"3181/3015 Mentor | 213/1373 Alum | CSA/FTAA/Jack-of-all-Trades","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3266873,"name":"NickRandom","username":"NickRandom","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/cc9497/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-12-19T05:24:27.834Z","cooked":"<p>It is hard to know without seeing some code, but I‚Äôll take a guess. If you have followed the WPILib swervebot example (also any of the other code I‚Äôve ever seen) then you will have a SwerveModule class with a SetDesiredState() function.</p>
<p>When there is no joystick input the state for each module will have zero speed, but will also have 0 angle (because it has to have some angle and that is what the maths will give you). In this case you want to set the driving motor to zero speed, but also you want to set the steering motor to zero speed, rather than driving to 0 angle.</p>
<p>I‚Äôm guessing that you are missing a check for zero speed and so you are driving the wheels to 0 angle when the joystick input stops. In my team‚Äôs software the relevent code looks like this. (C++ but hopefully you can get the idea).</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">void SwerveModule::SetDesiredState(const frc::SwerveModuleState&amp; state, bool dry_steer_allowed) {
    // If speed is zero and we are not doing dry steering, set motor outputs to zero and do nothing else
    if (state.speed == 0.0_mps) {
        m_drive_controller.Set(ControlMode::PercentOutput, 0.0);
        if (!dry_steer_allowed) {
            m_steer_controller.Set(ControlMode::PercentOutput, 0.0);
            return;
        }
    }


</code></pre>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":24,"updated_at":"2023-12-19T05:24:27.834Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":9,"reads":290,"readers_count":289,"score":108.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":446559,"topic_slug":"stopping-swerve-wheels-from-resetting-their-position-after-every-joystick-input","display_username":"NickRandom","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":32158,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"6996 Software Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/stopping-swerve-wheels-from-resetting-their-position-after-every-joystick-input/446559/3","custom_user_title":"6996 Software Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3267003,"name":"Andy Gasser","username":"gdefender","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gdefender/{size}/168507_2.png","created_at":"2023-12-19T15:11:25.781Z","cooked":"<p>Maintaining the current module angle when the desired chassis speeds are zero is built in to the <code>SwerveDriveKinematics.toSwerveModuleStates</code> method. I think you‚Äôll need to do a little debugging.</p>
<p>My first thought is that you need a wider deadband on your controller, maybe when you‚Äôre ‚Äústopped‚Äù you‚Äôre still telling the wheels to move very slowly.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":24,"updated_at":"2023-12-19T15:11:25.781Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":221,"readers_count":220,"score":59.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":446559,"topic_slug":"stopping-swerve-wheels-from-resetting-their-position-after-every-joystick-input","display_username":"Andy Gasser","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":32158,"username":"NickRandom","name":"NickRandom","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/cc9497/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":44380,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/stopping-swerve-wheels-from-resetting-their-position-after-every-joystick-input/446559/4","custom_user_title":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3267009,"name":"Inuka Silva","username":"InukaSilva","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/inukasilva/{size}/204373_2.png","created_at":"2023-12-19T15:20:09.015Z","cooked":"<p>Here is our code: <a href="https://github.com/team1305/2023_Offseason_Rev_Swerve_Project" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">GitHub - team1305/2023_Offseason_Rev_Swerve_Project: 2023 offseason swerve project</a><br>
