<p>A larger value allows a faster rate of change. For your specific problem, it‚Äôs a matter of making sure speed/magnitude reaches zero at the same time or before the direction and rotation values. You could increase the magnitude rate limit, or decrease direction. I didn‚Äôt try rotation, so you might have to look at that too.</p>","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"posts_count":24,"updated_at":"2023-12-19T17:24:28.741Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":9,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":134,"readers_count":133,"score":41.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":446559,"topic_slug":"stopping-swerve-wheels-from-resetting-their-position-after-every-joystick-input","display_username":"Andy Gasser","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":44380,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/stopping-swerve-wheels-from-resetting-their-position-after-every-joystick-input/446559/10","custom_user_title":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3267276,"name":"Inuka Silva","username":"InukaSilva","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/inukasilva/{size}/204373_2.png","created_at":"2023-12-19T23:55:23.626Z","cooked":"<p>I think I will have to fiddle with the rotation Slew rate too. Last time I tested the code, if I rotated the robot it wouldn‚Äôt r